9c) Build a Tip Calculator app using several JavaFX components and learn how to respond to user
interactions with the GUI
1. First create one new FXML document(Test1.fxml) then right click on that select open with scene
builder and Design your tipcal.fxml file like following screen.

And give ids for some controls to using into back end.

2. Create another class for using the above scene builder controls in back-end
Mycontrol.java
package application;
//MyControl.java
import javafx.fxml.FXML;
import javafx.scene.control.*;
public class MyControl {
//linking front end id to backend for using the controls by @FXML
@FXML
private TextField priceField, tipField;
@FXML
private Button calculateButton;
@FXML
private Label resultLable;
@FXML

public void initialize() {
// Setup code, like setting initial values or event handlers
calculateButton.setOnAction(event -> tipCalculate());
}
private void tipCalculate() {
try {
double price = Double.parseDouble(priceField.getText());
double tipPercent = Double.parseDouble(tipField.getText());
if (price < 0 || tipPercent < 0) {
resultLable.setText("Please enter positive values.");
} else { double tipAmount = price * tipPercent / 100;
double totalAmount = price + tipAmount;
resultLable.setText("Tip: $" + String.format("%.2f", tipAmount) + ", Total: $" +
String.format("%.2f", totalAmount));
}
} catch (NumberFormatException ex) {
resultLable.setText("Please enter valid numbers.");
}
}
}

3. To add this MyControl.java file into tipcal.fxml by following attribute and add fx: before id
attribute of all controls:
fx:controller=” application.MyControl”
Here application is package and MyControl is class.

4.Load the tipcal.fxml into your application.
TipCalculator.java :
package application;
//TipCalculator.java
import javafx.application.Application;
import javafx.fxml.FXMLLoader;
import javafx.scene.Parent;
import javafx.scene.Scene;
import javafx.stage.Stage;

public class TipCalculator extends Application {
@Override
public void start(Stage primaryStage) throws Exception {
FXMLLoader loader = new FXMLLoader(getClass().getResource("tipcal.fxml"));
Parent root = loader.load();
primaryStage.setTitle("Tip calculator UI");
primaryStage.setScene(new Scene(root));
primaryStage.show();
}
public static void main(String[] args) {
launch(args);
}
}
5. Finally Run the application and you will get a following out:
